Hong Kong Stocks Fluctuate as Developers Fall, Insurers Gain

-- B y   K a n a   N i s h i z a w a
-- 
2011-04-06T01:54:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/hong-kong-stocks-fluctuate-as-developers-fall-insurers-gain.html
Hong Kong stocks fluctuated, as
Chinese property developers declined after the nation raised
 interest rates  to restrain inflation, while insurers climbed.  China Overseas Land & Investment Ltd. (688) , controlled by the
nation’s construction ministry, fell 2.8 percent, while  China
Resources Land Ltd. (1109) , a state-controlled developer, slid 1.9
percent. Ping An Insurance (Group) Co.,  China ’s second-largest
insurer, increased 2.2 percent. Anhui Conch Cement Co., China’s
biggest cement producer, rose 1.3 percent after saying its
profit may have more than doubled.  The  Hang Seng Index (HSI)  rose 0.1 percent to 24,170.37, after
falling as much as 0.2 percent. About as many stocks advanced as
declined on the 45-member gauge. The Hang Seng China Enterprises
Index of Chinese companies’ H shares increased 0.4 percent to
13,646.37.  Futures on the Hang Seng Index fell 0.1 percent to 24,166.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kana Nishizawa in Tokyo at 
